Summary output file for CONGO-2D

Definition of terms:
Stream Thrust = Mdot*Vel + Pexit*Aexit
Gross Thrust = Mdot*Vel + Pexit*Aexit - Pamb*Aexit
Stream Thrust = Gross Thrust when Pamb = 0 (vacuum)
Cfg = Nozzle Thrust Coefficient (Gross Isp/Ideal Isp)
C* = Characteristic Exhaust Velocity
CD = Discharge coefficient: Massflow 2D/ Massflow 1D
1D = Assumes input are axial
2D = Uses actual flow angles in calculation

Input parameters
R*  = Throat Radius (in)

Nozzle Type: Minimum Length Nozzle

Nozzle Geometry:	Axisymmetric Nozzle
Design Parameter:	PTotal/PExit = 15.9542
Throat Geometry created by two arcs of given radii.
Upstream Radius/R*:	1.5
Downstream Radius/R*:	0.8

Thermodynamic Inputs
Total Pressure (psia):	290.076
Total Temperature (R):	4591.26
Gamma:	1.27
Molecular Weight:	21.65
Ambient Pressure (psia):	15.9542

MOC Grid Parameters
Number of characteristic lines at the nozzle throat:	141
Maximum allowable angle between characteristics along wall (deg):	1
Number of RRCs to calculate above KERNEL (50-100):	15

The Initial Data Line is where the MOC calculation begins.
Its based on the upstream radius of curvature and gamma.
It is solved for using a method developed
by Kliegel and Levine. This method is based on a method
developed by Hall. Hall used cylindrical coordinates (R)
This method uses toroid coordinates (R+1). This method
does better for small upstream radii.

